column5: Headed out with my boss today out of St Williams. From 10 - 2 we never caught a fish besides a couple sunfish, moved around and finally found a little crater that was full of decent perch. Managed 25 in the pail at an average of 10 inches a piece. Only 6 throwback dinks and big fish of the day was 14 inches. Fish hit from about 2 til 5PM.  Almost all of them were caught on minnows but a few fell to worms when we ran out of minnows.  No more perch for me now til ice up. Bigger things on the agenda!
Yeah, I went to Port Dover, to check out the pier. Only 2 guys fishing, nothing to show fer it. Had a good perch and Walleye dinner at the local restaurant.
It was $9.95 fer the perch Dinner, but I added a Walleye fillet fer an extra $4.95.
